race.comment: RIDEAU (1) has a solid record over this six-furlong journey with a win and two placings from four starts and gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim. Only needs some luck navigating from the sticky alley to be playing a major role in the finish. KOBAYASTAR (6) saves her best form for her home circuit here and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Sure to prove tough to hold out. BIG DEMEANOR (4) resumes here but has revved up for this with a recent trial and is two from two over this track and trip. Can run a big race while fresh. SUPER TWENTY THREE (8) is yet to miss a place in four starts over this course and distance and gets the services of Wiggins in the irons. In the mix. BRAVE INTENT (13) best of the rest from the favourable draw.
